<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berov's Political Consultations Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berov's Political Consultations Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103173194 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3103173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During the period of 25-31 March Prime Minister 
Berov had working meetings with Ahmed Dogan, chairman of the 
parliamentary faction of the Movement for Rights and Freedoms 
[DPS]; Nora Ananieva, chairman of the Parliamentary Alliance for 
Social Democracy; and Zhan Videnov, chairman of the Bulgarian 
Socialist Party [BSP] Supreme Council; as well as with Stefan 
Bozhilov and Georgi Kostov, cochairmen of the parliamentary 
faction of the New Alliance for Democracy. 
  The prime minister insisted on speeding up the adoption of 
the amendments to the Law on Reorganizing and Privatizing the 
State and Municipal Enterprises, and assured the representatives 
of the National Assembly that the government is prepared to 
implement the mass privatization program. 
  Certain weaknesses in the work of certain governmental 
structures also were discussed. Prof. Berov proposed structural 
changes in the cabinet that will be discussed by the 
parliamentary factions. 
  The prime minister outlined his views on overcoming the 
crisis situation in the foreign currency market and stressed the 
government's determination to successfully complete negotiations 
on the country's foreign debt. 

</TEXT>

